
The hardware has been designed by Chris Jones, Martin-Jones Technology Ltd

See BioBand Hardware Description for the features.

The low power and small size may make this open hardware platform suitable for a
wide range of applications.


Component Data Sheets used:

STM32F103C6T6 Microcontroller
http://www.st.com/stonline/products/literature/ds/13587.pdf

LIS331DLH Accelerometer
http://www.st.com/stonline/products/literature/ds/15094/lis331dlh.pdf

LM95071 Temperature Sensor
http://www.national.com/ds/LM/LM95071.pdf

HY27UF084G2B NAND Flash Memory
http://www.hynix.com/datasheet/pdf/flash/HY27UF(08_16)4G2B%20(Rev0.4).pdf

Design files:
The design files hosted elsewhere on this project were created using Altium
Designer.

Manufacturing files:
The manufacturing files are in Gerber photoplotter format with Excel and CSV
format bills of materials.

XJTAG test scripts:
The BioBand was designed to be prodution-line tested using the XJTAG
boundary-scan test system. The 20-pin JTAG connector on the dongle board is
directly compatible with the XJTAG dongle.
